org.sedml.modelsupport
Class SBMLSupport

java.lang.Object
  org.sedml.modelsupport.SBMLSupport

public class SBMLSupport
extends Object

Class to provide general support for working with SBML models, especially for the construction of XPath strings for use in Change and DataGenerator elements. Currently this class provides support for identifying global parameters, species and compartments, and some mutable attributes.

This class also provide some useful SBML related constants and static methods to create standard SBML math csymbols.

Author:
radams

createTimeSymbolNode

public static ASTSymbol createTimeSymbolNode()

Convenience method to create an ASTNode corresponding to the XML:

 <csymbol encoding="text" definitionURL="http://www.sbml.org/sbml/symbols/time">time <csymbol>

Returns:
an ASTNode referring to the standard symbol time

getLanguageFor

public SUPPORTED_LANGUAGE getLanguageFor(int level,
                                         int version)
Returns a SUPPORTED_LANGUAGE constant corresponding to a level/version combination supplied as arguments.

Parameters:
level - An SBML level
version - An SBML version
Returns:
The SUPPORTED_LANGUAGE constant referring to the supplied values. If the level and version do not correpsond to a correct SBML Version,SUPPORTED_LANGUAGE.SBML_GENERIC will be returned.
